[SN]TITLE[SN]
Appeal over man's 'unexplained' serious injuries in Peterhead

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have appealed for information after a man was found with "unexplained" serious injuries in Peterhead.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 56-year-old was taken to Aberdeen Royal Infirmary on Thursday afternoon.
Police said he had been in the Peter Buchan Drive area - and possibly Katterburn Court - between 23:00 on Wednesday and 02:00 on Thursday.
He is described as white, 6ft 1in tall, and slim. He has cropped grey hair and was unshaven.
